
1/ Install docker ce

	https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/

2/ Build dapp-java image

	sudo docker build -t dapp-java:latest .

3/ Run dapp-java container

	sudo docker run -it --memory=100m --memory-swap="200m" --cpus="0.01" --storage-opt size=120m -v $PDX_HOME/dapps:/dapps/ dapp-java HelloWorld.jar

	Here, the storage, memory and cpu limits are from chaincode deployment requirements. 
	The cost of deploying and invoking a dapp proportionately correlates to the 
	memory, cpu, disk and network requirements.
 
